  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Rub the kabocha squash with olive oil and season with salt, black pepper, and mustard seeds.",
    "Place the squash on a baking sheet and roast for 45 minutes, or until tender.",
    "While the squash is roasting, mix the Greek yogurt, chopped parsley, and grated cheddar cheese in a bowl.",
    "Once the squash is done, let it cool slightly, then chop it into small pieces and add it to the yogurt mixture.",
    "Stir in the crushed red pepper and lemon juice, then serve the hash hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired.",
    "Reheat the hash in the oven or on the stovetop before serving.",
    "Serve the hash with additional Greek yogurt or cheddar cheese on top, if desired."
